+## Correctness
+
+All acceptance criteria are met:
+
+**Master policy targets:** `MasteringPolicy` captures `target_lufs`, `target_lufs_range`, `true_peak_range_dbtp`, `limiter_ceiling_dbtp`, `eq_intent` (via `MasterEqIntent`), and `dynamic_contrast_db`. All 5 cadence states (`sleep`, `wind_down`, `wake_ramp`, `occupied_day`, `away_practice`) have explicit lookup entries. All 5 phases (`Divination`, `Emergence`, `Conversation`, `Convergence`, `Crystallization`) have distinct `_PHASE_MASTER_CONTRAST` values with correct ordering (Conversation narrowest, Divination/Crystallization widest). The sleep/wind_down +2 dB contrast bonus is applied correctly before the 24 dB cap.
+
+**Limiter ceiling consistency:** `build_mix_profile` now sets `peak_ceiling_dbtp = mastering.limiter_ceiling_dbtp` instead of hardcoding `-1.0`, and `verify_mix_profile` cross-checks both fields agree — preventing silent drift.
+
+**Low-end runaway proxy:** `check_low_end_runaway` implements a first-order IIR lowpass (correct RC formula) followed by linear-domain ratio comparison, with a minimum low-RMS floor to suppress false positives on near-silence signals. Logic is correct.
+
+**Automated proxies:** All four proxy checks are implemented: `check_clipping`, `check_silence`, `check_harshness_proxy`, `check_low_end_runaway`.
+
+**verify_mastering_policy bounds:** Checks all five fields — LUFS target/range coherence, true-peak range, limiter ceiling within peak range and ≤ −1.0 dBTP, EQ intent (low_cut 25–60 Hz, low_shelf ≤ 0.5 dB, presence/air ±2 dB), dynamic contrast 8–24 dB. Bogus-policy test confirms all five issue fields are raised.
+
+## Completeness
+
+- Unknown cadence states fall back to safe defaults (`target_lufs=-16.5`, `true_peak_range=(-3.5,-1.0)`, `-1.0` limiter, neutral EQ). No panic path.
+- Unknown phase names default to `Emergence` contrast.
+- `verify_mix_profile` cross-checks both `target_lufs` and `peak_ceiling_dbtp` against mastering policy, catching silent divergence.
+- `TestVerifyMixProfile::test_mastering_policies_pass_for_all_states_and_phases` exercises all 25 cadence/phase combinations.
+- Hardening item — revise_score integration: `tracker_compiler.py` imports and calls `revise_score` at line 17/1083; `duet_composer.py` does the same at line 80/838. `tests/test_self_critique.py::TestPipelineIntegration::test_tracker_compiler_uses_revise_score` asserts the call occurs during compilation. Pre-existing, addressed in T-021.
+- Hardening item — budget enforcement in tracker_solo_song: `grain_density`, `density_multiplier`, and `dsp_blocks_allowed` are all enforced in `duet_composer.py` lines 972–983, 756–761, 777–783. Pre-existing, addressed in prior tasks.
+- Hardening item — bootstrap_identity: Flagged as out of scope for this task family consistently in ESCALATIONS.md (T-021 through T-025). No startup-path code was touched by T-003.
+
+## Consistency
+
+Follows established patterns from T-001 and T-002:
+- New types are frozen dataclasses in `mix_engine.py`.
+- Build function signature uses keyword-only args matching `build_dynamics_profile` / `build_spatial_profile`.
+- `MixProfile` field added as optional (`mastering: MasteringPolicy | None = None`), consistent with `dynamics` and `spatial`.
+- Verification wired into `verify_mix_profile()` via `issues.extend(...)`, consistent with how dynamics/spatial issues would be added.
+- Test classes follow `class TestFoo:` pattern with descriptive method names.
+
+## Security
+
+No concerns. All new code is pure computation with no I/O, no subprocess calls, no external dependencies, and no secrets. No attack surface introduced.
+
+## Quality
+
+- **Test suite:** 2271 passed, 0 failures, 0 errors. No regressions introduced.
+- **T-003 specific tests:** `test_mastering_policy_attached_to_mix_profile`, `test_mastering_policy_installation_safe_for_all_cadences`, `test_mastering_dynamic_contrast_is_phase_specific`, `TestLowEndRunaway::test_balanced_signal_is_clean`, `TestLowEndRunaway::test_sub_heavy_signal_is_flagged`, `test_mastering_policies_pass_for_all_states_and_phases`, `test_bogus_mastering_policy_caught` — all pass.
+- Dynamic contrast ordering test confirms `Conversation < Divination` and `Conversation < Crystallization` for the same cadence state.
+- Low-end runaway test uses realistic amplitude ratios (0.75 sub vs 0.05 full-band) to confirm the proxy fires on genuinely pathological signals.
+
+## Issues Found
+
+None.
+
+## Verdict: PASS
